  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why don't some people use social media at all?",
  "response": "There are various reasons why some people choose not to use social media:\n\n1. **Privacy Concerns**: Many people are worried about their personal information being exposed or misused. Social media platforms often collect and share user data, which can lead to privacy breaches.\n\n2. **Mental Health**: Social media can sometimes contribute to anxiety, stress, and depression. The constant comparison with others and exposure to negative content can adversely affect mental well-being.\n\n3. **Time Consumption**: Social media can be very time-consuming and addictive. Some people prefer to invest their time in other activities such as hobbies, spending time with family, or engaging in physical activities.\n\n4. **Information Overload**: The sheer amount of information on social media can be overwhelming. Some people prefer to avoid the constant barrage of news, advertisements, and updates.\n\n5. **Personal Preference**: Some individuals simply do not enjoy using social media. They may prefer face-to-face interactions or other methods of communication.\n\n6. **Misinformation and Polarization**: Social media platforms can sometimes spread misinformation and contribute to societal polarization. Some people choose to abstain from social media to avoid these issues.\n\n7. **Professional Reasons**: Certain professions may require maintaining a low online profile for security or other reasons.\n\n8. **Cultural or Social Norms**: In some cultures or social groups, social media use may not be prevalent or may even be discouraged.\n\n9. **Digital Detox**: Some people actively choose to disconnect from digital platforms to pursue a more balanced lifestyle.\n\nEveryone has their individual reasons, and these are just some common factors that might influence someone\u2019s decision to stay off social media.",
